CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 8, 1973, pg. 2 reads: "Back to Baxter - This scene was typical of many throughout the country when millions of youngsters returned to school after enjoying a nice, long summer vacation.  it was back to Baxter School in Homewood from the youngsters pictured above.  Some young mothers are pictured in the group as they accompanied small fry to the elementary school. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of mothers and children gathered outside of Baxter Elementary School for the first day of school, Homewood
